                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/138: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-19T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2346. For the Secretary of State.</p>
                <p>Referring to Department’s 2315, June 16, 4 p.m.<note n="8" xml:id="d402fn8">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_379">p. 379</ref>.</note> Mr.
                        <persName>Znamensky</persName>, who states he is Assistant Minister of Food
                    and Supplies for the Russian Government at Omsk, desires to purchase uniforms
                    and overcoats or cloth for manufacture thereof; underwear, stockings, shoes,
                    caps, et cetera; machinery, tools, rations, motor vehicles and other supplies,
                    excepting munitions of war.</p>
                <p>Russian Embassy here inform me his credentials authentic. He proposes payment
                    upon credit basis or by a loan or such other method of payment and security as
                    may prove acceptable.</p>
                <p>What attitude is Department to assume? …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
